Attributes.Value: How did you get involved as an online instructor at [PSI]?
Tell me about the orientation process for new faculty in the online ECE program. What does your orientation package consist of?
Anything about the orientation process that could be improved?
Do you have sufficient resources/supplies to teach online effectively? If not, what else do you need?
How are you evaluated as an instructor? (Student evaluations, supervisor assessments)
How is feedback shared and used by yourself and how is it used by yourself? How is it used by [PSI]?
What professional development activities do you need/want/look for? (ex. Internal to [PSI] Pro-d, External to [PSI]).
Does [PSI] provide you with additional time for pro-d within your schedule (paid)? Or, is this to be completed on your own time (unpaid)?
Tell me about the opportunities you have to provide feedback on curriculum, texts, equipment, online platform.
How do you address student attendance and student engagement online?
How do you communicate with your students? (i.e. noticing student progression in a course, assignment quality, practice in the field etc.)
How do students communicate with each other in class? (i.e. evidence of student engagement, teamwork).
What is communication like between practicum and theoretical instructors?
What communication do you need from the program coordinator/chair? Are you receiving it?
Tell us about the practicums students complete (How do they get paired with a site? What types of programs? Locations? Etc.)
Are students admitted to the online program likely to be successful in the ECE field? Why?
What are the strengths of the online program?
How could the online program be improved? Why?
Is there any other information you would like to share?
If PSI has both online and face-to-face offerings: What kind of interaction do you have with face-to-face offerings?
Are there any differences you see between the online versus face-to-face offerings? (ex: demographic of students admitted, success rates, part-time versus full time enrollment, engagement, etc.)

How and why did you select this post-secondary institution/online ECE program? (Prompting questions, if needed: Did you look at any other ECE programs? Did you look at any face-to-face programs or only considered online?)

Tell us about the admissions process and your orientation to the expectations of the online program.  (Prompting questions, if needed: On your initial contact with the school, were you given a complete description of the program (schedule, student expectations) and the operation of the school (resources, facilities, school policies))?
Tell us about the opportunities you are provided to evaluate instructors/course materials, texts, equipment, the online learning platform, etc .
Any examples you can share where you have seen your feedback/evaluations lead to change within the program?
Tell us about opportunities to connect with other students in the online program.
Does the course outline match with what you experience in class?
How engaged do you feel with the content/your peers/the instructor in the online environment?
Do you feel you have adequate resources in the online program (materials, texts, library, access to instructors, tech support)?
If you had a concern about an instructor, online accessibility or course material, who would you go to?
What is working well in the online program?
How could [PSI] improve the online program?  (Prompting themes: Pacing/order of course content, instructors capabilities, etc.)
Have you experienced any technical difficulties while taking the online course? If so, tell me about the process to fix the problem.
